3. Technical Architecture Specifications
3.1 Component Topology
- caaa-applet (GUI): Native Rust binary using libcosmic. Runs in user session. Displays STATUS_BLOCK and chat UI. Communicates via gRPC over localhost Unix socket.
- caaa-core (Daemon): Headless Rust binary. Manages state, orchestrates LLM/Prolog, handles vault I/O. Runs as user systemd service.
- caaa-reasoning (Library): Embedded Prolog/Lisp engines for symbolic logic. Linked statically into core.
- caaa-vault (Library): Safe wrappers for Obsidian markdown manipulation. Enforces atomic writes.
- Transport: gRPC over Unix Domain Socket (/run/user/UID/caaa.sock) protected by mTLS.
3.2 gRPC Service Definition (caaa.proto)
protobuf
syntax = "proto3";
package caaa.v1;
service CAAACore {
  // Stream chat messages; server streams back tokens
  rpc ChatStream(stream ChatRequest) returns (stream ChatResponse);
  // Get deterministic status block (No LLM involved)
  rpc GetStatus(Empty) returns (StatusBlock);
  // Query Obsidian vault
  rpc SearchVault(SearchQuery) returns (VaultResults);
  // Execute vault write (Audited)
  rpc WriteNote(NoteEdit) returns (WriteReceipt);
  // System control
  rpc SwitchModel(ModelRequest) returns (ModelStatus);
}
message StatusBlock {
  string active_model = 1;
  int32 context_window_usage = 2;
  bool vault_integrity_ok = 3;
  string constitutional_mode = 4; // "STRICT", "ADVISORY", "OFF"
  uint64 uptime_seconds = 5;
  string error_state = 6; // Empty if healthy
}
message ChatRequest {
  string session_id = 1;
  string content = 2;
  optional ContextHint hint = 3;
}
message ChatResponse {
  oneof response {
    string token_delta = 1;
    string final_verdict = 2; // From Constitutional Layer
    bool stopped = 3;
  }
}

3.3 Data Flow: Chat Turn
1\. Input: User types in Applet -> ChatRequest sent via gRPC.
2\. Ingestion: Core receives request, logs to Audit Thread (write-ahead log).
3\. Context: Core retrieves relevant Obsidian notes via caaa-vault.
4\. Reasoning:
- LLM generates draft response.
- caaa-reasoning runs Prolog constraints on draft.
- If violation detected, draft is rejected/modified based on Constitution.
5\. Output: Stream tokens back to Applet.
6\. Finalize: Audit Thread commits final exchange to persistent state and updates STATUS_BLOCK.
3.4 Critical Invariants
- Invariant A: STATUS_BLOCK fields are NEVER generated by LLM. They are direct reads of system metrics and state flags.
- Invariant B: Vault writes occur ONLY via the Audit Thread. No other process holds write locks.
- Invariant C: All gRPC traffic must present valid client certificates signed by the local Root CA.
